import java.util.*;

public class Q1 {
    static class LRUCache extends LinkedHashMap<Integer,Integer> {
        private final int capacity;
        LRUCache(int capacity) {
            super(capacity, 0.75f, true); // accessOrder=true
            this.capacity = capacity;
        }
        public int get(int key) { return super.getOrDefault(key, -1); }
        public void put(int key, int value) { super.put(key, value); }
        @Override protected boolean removeEldestEntry(Map.Entry<Integer,Integer> e) {
            return size() > capacity;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        LRUCache cache = new LRUCache(2);
        cache.put(1, 1); cache.put(2, 2);
        System.out.println(cache.get(1)); // 1 (now most recently used)
        cache.put(3, 3);                  // evicts 2 (least recently used)
        System.out.println(cache.get(2)); // -1
        System.out.println(cache.get(3)); // 3
    }
}

problems.description:
Implement a Fixed Window Rate Limiter.

```java
public class FixedWindowRateLimiter {
    private final int maxRequests;
    private final long windowMs;
    private final Map<String, int[]> counters = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
    // int[0]=count, int[1]=windowStart (millis)

    public boolean allow(String clientId) {
        long now = System.currentTimeMillis();
        counters.compute(clientId, (k, v) -> {
            if (v == null || now - v[1] >= windowMs)
                return new int[]{1, (int)now};
            v[0]++;
            return v;
        });
        return counters.get(clientId)[0] <= maxRequests;
    }
}
```

**Example (10 req/min):**
First 10 requests: allowed
11th request in same window: denied (429)
After window resets: allowed again

**Key insight:** Fixed window is simple but has boundary burst (10 + 10 = 20 requests in 2 seconds across window boundary). Sliding window or token bucket fix this.

